lly\npopulated by optical/UV TDEs that most likely produce X-rays, but due to\nreprocessing this emission is \"veiled\" from observations. Our results suggest\nthat non-jetted X-ray TDEs likely originate from partial disruptions and/or\ndisruptions of low mass stars.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 7 Nov 2016 21:00:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 10 Jan 2017 15:42:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-04-12"}
